Reasoning: The paper discusses database technologies and their characteristics for handling big data, specifically focusing on NewSQL databases for online transaction processing. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DB (Databases), followed by cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.SE (Software Engineering). The paper also touches upon distributed computing (cs.DC) and programming languages (cs.PL) in the context of comparing different database technologies.
